david lang program events at stanford david lang program facebook twitter email print add to calendar sure to be one of the most talked about events of the season paul hillier's acclaimed a cappella theatre of voices makes a rare appearance outside europe sharing the program with four celebrated and artistically diverse musicians each equally respected in the worlds of pop and new music bryce dessner of the national shara worden of my brightest diamond nico muhly and owen pallett the music is all by david lang stanford 78 including the bracing contemplative little match girl passion which earned lang the pulitzer prize and theatre of voices a grammy and the world premiere of death speaks a lively arts commissioned companion work that the composer imagines full of post folk darkness and introspection program lang little match girl passion 2007 death speaks 2011 world premiere when wednesday january 25 2012 8 00 pm where dinkelspiel auditorium map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags performance music arts sponsor stanford lively arts contact 650 725 arts 2787 livelyarts stanford edu admission reserved seating $44 50 permalink http events stanford edu events 284 28477 more info last modified november 17 2011
